U.K Police Arrest 25-Year-Old Man in Computer Hacking Probe

-- B y   K i t   C h e l l e l
-- 
2011-08-03T17:36:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/u-k-police-arrest-25-year-old-man-in-computer-hacking-probe.html
A 25-year-old man was charged by U.K.
police investigating an attempt by computer hackers to access
Facebook Inc.’s website.  Glenn Steven Mangham, who lives in York,  England , was
charged with unauthorized access to computer material,
unauthorized acts with intent to impair the operation of a
computer, and making, supplying or obtaining articles for use in
an offense under the computer misuse act. He is due to appear at
City of Westminster Magistrates’ Court on Aug. 17.  The Metropolitan Police’s e-Crime unit is separately
prosecuting two British teenagers accused of hacking into the
Serious Organised Crime Agency’s computer system.  To contact the reporter for this story:
Kit Chellel in London 
 cchellel@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Anthony Aarons at   aaarons@bloomberg.net . 